What you need to know:

The Nigerian Army on September 21 confirmed the killing of Col Dahiru U Bako, the commander of 25 Task Force Brigade in Damboa in Borno State, where Nigeria Army’s Operation Lafiya Dole has been battling terrorists. No fewer than 30,000 people have been killed in the insurgency in Borno, Adamawa and Yobe states in northeast since 2009. 